We average the 2012 and 2017 residential population within rural electrification pixels for each Indian state to estimate the population that benefited from infrastructure investments, and compare these estimates to the number of Indian residents that gained electricity access between 2011 and 2016 from the national surveys. This number is derived by differencing the electrified population in the 2011 census (Indian Census Bureau and Sou, 2011) from that in the 2015–2016 National Family Health Survey (International Institute f, 2016) for each Indian state (Population2016, state*%Elec2016, state
                        -Population2011, state*%Elec2011, state
                        ).
